In this article, President Trump and Crown Prince bin Salman of Saudi Arabia discuss their countries' relationship and various business deals. They emphasize the economic benefits and job creation resulting from Saudi investments in the US, particularly in the defense sector. They also mention their joint efforts to combat terrorism and the importance of not funding terrorist activities. President Trump mentions the bombings in Austin, Texas, expressing his commitment to finding the perpetrators. He also briefly mentions his call with President Putin of Russia, where they discussed arms control and other international issues. President Trump hints at the upcoming decision on the Iran nuclear deal, stating that Iran has not been behaving appropriately and that the world will see what action he takes.